                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12922602" author="faywang" created="Tue, 19 Oct 2010 17:02:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The two flags in OracleDictionary:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        maxEmbeddedBlobSize = 4000;&lt;br/&gt;
        maxEmbeddedClobSize = 4000;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;are intended for applications using pre-11.2.0.1 jdbc driver. When these flags are set, MaxEmbeddedLobFieldStrategy will be used as for any Lob fields. The Lob field can appear in an Embeddable, which may be an element in the ElementCollection. It can also be a field in an entity.  The above exception is thrown when the Lob field is in an Embeddable and the embeddable is an element of an ElementCollection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The limitation of 4000 is fixed in jdbc driver 11.2.0.1. The patch for this JIRA is to fix the exception for applications which still use pre-11.2.0.1 driver. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
